{"id":507,"date":"2024-07-15T10:36:56","date_gmt":"2024-07-15T15:36:56","guid":{"rendered":"https://endhazing.sl.ua.edu/?page_id=507"},"modified":"2025-05-19T09:23:33","modified_gmt":"2025-05-19T14:23:33","slug":"how-to-prevent","status":"publish","type":"page","link":"https://endhazing.sl.ua.edu/prevent-it/how-to-prevent/","title":{"rendered":"How to Prevent"},"content":{"rendered":"\n<p>The fight against hazing is everyone&#8217;s responsibility, and we&#8217;ve organized some tips here for students and community members to know how to respond and proactively prevent hazing. </p>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-group alignfull is-style-elevated is-layout-constrained wp-block-group-is-layout-constrained\" id=\"speakUp\" style=\"margin-top:var(--wp--preset--spacing--flow-double);margin-bottom:var(--wp--preset--spacing--flow-double);padding-top:var(--wp--preset--spacing--flow-double);padding-bottom:var(--wp--preset--spacing--flow-double)\">\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Speak Up</h2>\n\n\n\n<p>The first step to ending hazing is to identify it and make your voice heard.</p>\n\n\n\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Ask Questions &#8211; Be Direct</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>Ask specific, clarifying questions if you see something that could be considered hazing.</p>\n\n\n\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li>“I noticed you missed last night’s meeting. You look like you’re tired and in pain, is everything ok?”</li>\n\n\n\n<li>“I saw you wearing a funny outfit in class today. Did someone force you to wear that?”</li>\n\n\n\n<li>“You haven’t turned in your homework and your grades dropped, what’s going on?”</li>\n\n\n\n<li>“Why do you have so many bruises on you? Did someone hit you?”</li>\n\n\n\n<li>“How did that symbol appear on your skin? Were you branded?”</li>\n\n\n\n<li>“We haven’t seen you in a few weeks, where have you been? Are you being forced to self-isolate?”</li>\n\n\n\n<li>“Why are people calling you that derogatory nickname?”</li>\n</ul>\n\n\n\n<p>Remember, these conversations will always be situational and contextual. You are more likely to get an honest response if the person you’re asking trusts you. Even if they insist they are not being hazed, hazing occurs with and without the victim’s consent.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Use your voice to speak up and identify hazing when it happens.</p>\n</div>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-group alignfull is-style-default is-layout-constrained wp-block-group-is-layout-constrained\" id=\"preventionTraining\" style=\"margin-top:var(--wp--preset--spacing--flow-double);margin-bottom:var(--wp--preset--spacing--flow-double);padding-top:var(--wp--preset--spacing--flow);padding-bottom:var(--wp--preset--spacing--flow)\">\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Hazing Prevention Training</h2>\n\n\n\n<p>Select the button below to complete the free online Vector Solutions LMS training for hazing prevention. The full course is approximately 27 minutes long.</p>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-buttons is-layout-flex wp-block-buttons-is-layout-flex\">\n<div class=\"wp-block-button\"><a class=\"wp-block-button__link wp-element-button\" href=\"http://uastudents-al.safecolleges.com/courses/details/28C6A65C-7401-11EC-97AA-456D67F96AF6?splash=0(opens%20in%20a%20new%20tab)\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">Vector Solutions Hazing Prevention Training</a></div>\n</div>\n</div>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-group alignfull is-style-prominent is-layout-constrained wp-container-core-group-is-layout-c160b77e wp-block-group-is-layout-constrained\" id=\"activities\" style=\"margin-top:0;margin-bottom:0;padding-top:0;padding-bottom:0\"><div class=\"wp-block-cover alignfull has-parallax has-background\" style=\"margin-top:0;margin-bottom:0\"><div class=\"wp-block-cover__image-background wp-image-317 has-parallax\" role=\"img\" aria-label=\"Seven students in Greek-letter organization shirts pose together on an outdoor basketball court, representing campus community and organizational pride.\" style=\"background-position:50% 50%;background-image:url(https://endhazing.sl.ua.edu/wp-content/uploads/sites/11/2025/gsu-life/gsu-place-and-family.png?v=20260414)\"></div><span aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"wp-block-cover__background has-black-background-color has-background-dim\"></span><div class=\"wp-block-cover__inner-container is-layout-constrained wp-block-cover-is-layout-constrained\">\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading has-text-align-center\">Alternate Activities</h2>\n<p class=\"has-text-align-center\">There are multiple ways for members of a social organization to bond with one another that don&#8217;t involve hazing or actions related to hazing. Below are a few alternative options in the Lincoln Parish Area available to social organizations that allow members to grow with one another.</p>\n<div class=\"gram-alt-activities\">\n<details>\n<summary>Outdoor and nature activities</summary>\n<div class=\"gram-alt-panel\">\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"https://www.google.com/maps/search/?api=1&amp;query=Lincoln+Parish+Park+Ruston+LA\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">Lincoln Parish Park</a> — trails, swimming, biking, picnics</li>\n<li><a href=\"https://www.lastateparks.com/parks-preserves/jimmie-davis-state-park\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">Jimmie Davis State Park</a> — camping, hiking, lake activities</li>\n<li><a href=\"https://www.google.com/maps/search/?api=1&amp;query=downtown+Ruston+LA+murals\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">Ruston downtown murals walk</a> — public art in the city center</li>\n<li><a href=\"https://www.google.com/maps/search/?api=1&amp;query=Mitcham+Farms+Louisiana\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">Mitcham Farms</a> — seasonal produce and outdoor events (confirm hours seasonally)</li>\n<li>Rock climbing or bouldering — search <a href=\"https://www.google.com/maps/search/?api=1&amp;query=climbing+gym+Ruston+LA+Monroe+LA\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">climbing gyms in Ruston or Monroe</a></li>\n<li>Group nature photo challenge — pick a trail or downtown route together</li>\n<li>Outdoor yoga or stretching — organize at a public park (check park rules)</li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n</details>\n<details>\n<summary>Cultural and educational activities</summary>\n<div class=\"gram-alt-panel\">\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"https://www.google.com/maps/search/?api=1&amp;query=Eddie+G+Robinson+Museum+Grambling+LA\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">Eddie G. Robinson Museum</a> — sports heritage (verify hours)</li>\n<li><a href=\"https://www.lastateparks.com/historic-sites/autrey-house-museum\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">Autrey House Museum</a> — historic site near Dubach</li>\n<li><a href=\"https://www.gram.edu/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">Grambling State University</a> — campus art shows, lectures, and student programs (see university calendar)</li>\n<li><a href=\"https://www.lopal.org/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">Lincoln Parish Library</a> — workshops and community programs</li>\n<li>International or cultural nights — watch <a href=\"https://www.gram.edu/student-life/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">Student Life</a> and student organization listings</li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n</details>\n<details>\n<summary>Community and service activities</summary>\n<div class=\"gram-alt-panel\">\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"https://www.google.com/maps/search/?api=1&amp;query=Ruston+LA+farmers+market\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">Ruston Farmers Market</a> — volunteer or shop together (confirm schedule)</li>\n<li><a href=\"https://www.louisianapeachfest.org/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">Louisiana Peach Festival</a> and other <a href=\"https://www.ruston.org/events/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">Ruston-area events</a></li>\n<li>Community clean-ups or park beautification — partner with local government or nonprofits</li>\n<li>Service projects — contact churches, food pantries, or <a href=\"https://www.google.com/maps/search/?api=1&amp;query=nonprofit+Ruston+LA\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">nonprofits in Ruston</a></li>\n<li>Food drives and charity events — coordinate with campus groups or local charities</li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n</details>\n<details>\n<summary>Food, coffee, and social hangouts</summary>\n<div class=\"gram-alt-panel\">\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"https://www.google.com/maps/search/?api=1&amp;query=downtown+Ruston+LA+restaurants\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">Downtown Ruston dining</a> — small-group restaurant crawl</li>\n<li><a href=\"https://www.google.com/maps/search/?api=1&amp;query=coffee+shop+Ruston+LA\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">Coffee shop meetups</a> in Ruston or Grambling</li>\n<li>Group cooking or baking night — use farmers market or grocery ingredients</li>\n<li><a href=\"https://www.google.com/maps/search/?api=1&amp;query=bakery+ice+cream+Ruston+LA\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">Local bakeries and dessert spots</a> — plan a walking dessert tour</li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n</details>\n<details>\n<summary>Recreation and fun group activities</summary>\n<div class=\"gram-alt-panel\">\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"https://www.google.com/maps/search/?api=1&amp;query=bowling+Ruston+LA\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">Bowling</a> in the Ruston area</li>\n<li><a href=\"https://www.google.com/maps/search/?api=1&amp;query=escape+room+Monroe+LA\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">Escape rooms</a> in Monroe (short drive)</li>\n<li>Game night — board games, trivia, or team competitions on campus</li>\n<li><a href=\"https://www.google.com/maps/search/?api=1&amp;query=movie+theater+Ruston+LA\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">Movie theaters</a> near Ruston</li>\n<li>Group fitness — <a href=\"https://www.gram.edu/student-life/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">campus recreation</a> or local studios (search Zumba, spin, kickboxing)</li>\n<li>Intramural scrimmages — volleyball, soccer, basketball through university recreation</li>\n<li>Scavenger hunt — design one across GSU campus or downtown Ruston</li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n</details>\n<details>\n<summary>Events and entertainment</summary>\n<div class=\"gram-alt-panel\">\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"https://www.ruston.org/events/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">Ruston community calendar</a> and regional festivals</li>\n<li><a href=\"https://gsutigers.com/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">GSU athletics</a> — baseball, football, basketball, and more</li>\n<li>Community art nights or craft workshops — watch city and campus calendars</li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n</details>\n</div>\n</div></div></div>\n","protected":false},"excerpt":{"rendered":"<p>The fight against hazing is everyone&#8217;s responsibility, and we&#8217;ve organized some tips here for students and community members to know how to respond and proactively prevent hazing. Speak Up The first step to ending hazing is to identify it and make your voice heard. Ask Questions &#8211; Be Direct Ask specific, clarifying questions if you [&hellip;]</p>\n","protected":false},"author":4,"featured_media":0,"parent":30,"menu_order":0,"comment_status":"closed","ping_status":"closed","template":"page-content-margin-0-bottom.php","meta":{"hero_blocks":"","sidebar_menu":"","sidebar":false,"sidebar_type":"select","hero":false,"title_alignment":"left","title_width":"standard","footnotes":""},"class_list":["post-507","page","type-page","status-publish","hentry"],"_links":{"self":[{"href":"https://endhazing.sl.ua.edu/wp-json/wp/v2/pages/507","targetHints":{"allow":["GET"]}}],"collection":[{"href":"https://endhazing.sl.ua.edu/wp-json/wp/v2/pages"}],"about":[{"href":"https://endhazing.sl.ua.edu/wp-json/wp/v2/types/page"}],"author":[{"embeddable":true,"href":"https://endhazing.sl.ua.edu/wp-json/wp/v2/users/4"}],"replies":[{"embeddable":true,"href":"https://endhazing.sl.ua.edu/wp-json/wp/v2/comments?post=507"}],"version-h